sentences: Evan Brewer (born September 23, 1981) is an American bass player from Nashville, Tennessee.
In 2011, he released his debut solo album titled Alone, and his second solo album, Your Itinerary, was released on July 16, 2013.

They have currently only released two songs; "Clock In & Die" and "Meet Me There".
In early 2011, he joined death metal band The Faceless after the departure of Brandon Giffin, who joined Cynic as a touring member.
Brewer also has a solo project under his own name, for which he has currently released two albums (Alone and Your Itinerary).
He chose to leave The Faceless in October 2014 to pursue other musical interests, such as recording the Primal EP with technical death metal band Entheos.
In September of 2020, he joined Nashville-based experimental rock collective Look
